                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Receptors detects stimulus</li>
                        <li>Sensory neurone sends impulse, to relay neurone through synapse</li>
                        <li>The relay neurone sends impulse to the CNS (brain)</li>
                        <li>The CNS processes the input</li>
                        <li>The CNS sends impulse to the motor neurone</li>
                        <li>The motor neurone sends impulse to the effector</li>
                        <li>The effector carries out the action</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>The stimulus is detected by receptors</li>
                        <li>Sensory neurone sends impulse, to relay neurone through synapse</li>
                        <li>The relay neurone sends impulse to the CNS (spinal cord)</li>
                        <li>The CNS processes the input, but subconsciously</li>
                        <li>The CNS sends impulse to the motor neurone</li>
                        <li>The motor neurone sends impulse to the effector</li>
                        <li>The effector carries out the action</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </Table>
